    localContent: `<p>904 Dumpster delivers 20 yard roll-off containers across the Jacksonville metro from a local depot in Duval County, with drive times under 45 minutes to every address in our service area. We cover urban neighborhoods like Riverside, San Marco, and Springfield; suburban areas including Mandarin, Southside, and the Northside; the Beaches corridor through Atlantic Beach, Neptune Beach, and Jacksonville Beach; and out to <a href="/dumpster-rental-ponte-vedra-fl" class="text-primary hover:underline" title="Dumpster Rental Ponte Vedra FL">Ponte Vedra</a>, <a href="/dumpster-rental-orange-park-fl" class="text-primary hover:underline" title="Dumpster Rental Orange Park FL">Orange Park</a>, and <a href="/dumpster-rental-fernandina-beach-fl" class="text-primary hover:underline" title="Dumpster Rental Fernandina Beach FL">Fernandina Beach</a>.</p><p>Disposal happens at <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trail_Ridge_Landfill" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline" title="Trail Ridge Landfill on Wikipedia">Trail Ridge Landfill</a> on the city's west side, the Duval County construction-and-demolition facility. Driveway placements within Jacksonville city limits don't require a permit. Street or right-of-way placements need a permit through the <a href="https://www.jacksonville.gov/departments/public-works.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline" title="City of Jacksonville Public Works">City of Jacksonville Public Works</a> office, which we'll help you coordinate when you book. For full local-area coverage and pricing, see the <a href="/dumpster-rental-pricing-jacksonville" class="text-primary hover:underline" title="Dumpster Rental Pricing Jacksonville">Jacksonville pricing page</a>.</p>`,
